  "text": "BLAST is fairly advanced among model checkers for software. It is also somewhat unique in this category in that it uses a sophisticated mix of techniques to perform the property check. It uses abstractions and counterexample-guided abstraction refinement (CEGAR) to make the checking efficient. It also employs theorem provers for constructing abstract state transitions and for checking the feasibility of error paths [CITATION_1] .",
